## Problema 1 <a name="1"></a>
**Enunciado:**
Termopares en
circuito lineal.
a)
$$\alpha_{ab} = 15$$
$$\mu\text{V/K}$$
$$\alpha_{ac} = 10$$
$$\mu\text{V/K}$$
$$T_1 = 1000$$
$$^{\circ}\text{C}$$
$$T_2 = 500$$
$$^{\circ}\text{C}$$
$$T_3 = 100$$
$$^{\circ}\text{C}$$
$$T_4 = 50$$
$$^{\circ}\text{C}$$
Calcular f.e.m.

**Solución:**
En Kelvin:
$$T_1 = 1273$$
$$\text{K}$$
$$T_2 = 773$$
$$\text{K}$$
$$T_3 = 373$$
$$\text{K}$$
$$T_4 = 523$$
$$\text{K}$$
Relaciones:
$$\alpha_{bc} = \alpha_{ac} - \alpha_{ab} = -5$$
$$\mu\text{V/K}$$
$$\alpha_{cb} = 5$$
$$\mu\text{V/K}$$
Fórmula:
$$\epsilon_T = -\alpha_{ab}T_1 + \alpha_{ac}T_2 + \alpha_{cb}T_4 - \alpha_{bc}T_2 - \alpha_{cb}T_3$$
Sustituyendo:
$$\epsilon_T = -15 \cdot 1273 + 10 \cdot 773 + 5 \cdot 523 - (-5) \cdot 773 - 5 \cdot 373$$
$$\epsilon_T = -7750$$
$$\mu\text{V}$$

